# kairos-llm-scorer route fragment for the shared edge (CLUSTER mode only).
#
# The edge knows only "scorer → its inner Caddy"; THIS file (owned by this repo)
# decides which hostnames the edge serves and where they go. The deploy hook
# drops it into the edge's conf.d/ and reloads the edge — see
# ../post-receive.sh. Standalone mode does not use this file.
#
# Target is the inner-Caddy alias this stack joins the `edge` network with
# (../docker-compose.yml): kairos-llm-scorer-inner.

# LAN surface — always available (local CA TLS).
scorer.cluster.lan {
	tls {
		issuer internal {
			lifetime 7d
		}
	}
	reverse_proxy kairos-llm-scorer-inner:80
}

# Public surface via an outbound tunnel. The tunnel daemon forwards decrypted
# requests to the edge :80 as plaintext (the http:// prefix serves cleartext +
# suppresses the auto-HTTPS 308).
#
# `import public_gate` wires this PUBLIC surface into the edge's cluster gate: when
# scorer.example.com is listed in EDGE_PUBLIC_BLOCK (the edge .env), the edge
# returns 403 here; unlisted = reachable. That gate is COARSE (all-or-nothing).
# The real authorized-vs-unauthorized check is the app's own API-key gate on
# POST /score (KAIROS_SCORER_API_KEYS) — set it before unblocking this surface.
# The LAN surface above is never gated.
http://scorer.example.com {
	import public_gate
	reverse_proxy kairos-llm-scorer-inner:80 {
		header_up X-Forwarded-Host scorer.example.com
		header_up X-Forwarded-Proto https
	}
}
